rComments: He is the best math teacher at UIUC. He made calculus so clear. Definitely take his class if you have a chance. However, because math220 is a 5 credit course, and he had so many stuffs to teach. Some students might think his lectures are too fast. But if you pay attention you will be fine. And really recommend to the past exams and quiz.

Great note provider, as long as you take the notes well, you will totally be fine. You can basically copy whatever he writes on the blackboard cuz it includes everything!  Grading is super fair too. He replaces the final grade with one of your lowest midterms and still get to keep the final grade for final.
Amazing lecturer. Passionate about math. Drops lowest two quizzes and will replace your lowest exam score with your final score. The exams are VERY difficult. Be prepared.
The best professor I have met till now.
Just a great supporter and a really clear professor during lectures.
By far the best math teacher I have ever had. Fantastic lectures that are actually enjoyable, tests are fair.
The test can be super hard. Get ready to do lots of practice.

Professor Murphy is a phenomenal educator. He provides both the resources and the insight necessary to master the material he covers. In a broader sense, he has a certain way about him that makes learning the subject he teaches (calculus 1) feel a worthwhile endeavor.

Great teacher. Very patient whenever you went to him for a math problem, personal issue, or a regrade. His class is very easy to understand because he was using a very formal, standard way to break down every problem and those problems will appear in tests and quizzes, nothing unexpected. He also posts all previous tests online for you to practice.
Very clear explanations and teaching.

He has online quizzes and exams from past semesters. USE THEM. I never read a page from the text book and I understood the material very well because of past exams and quizzes. He is very  strict on grading but will make you think you rock at calc (until you get to calc 2 with horrible professors).

As someone who doesn't really like Math, Bob Murphy is the best Math Teacher/Professor I have ever had.  Although I did pretty average in this class grade wise, I felt I understood the material way better than I ever had before in any other math.  This class is a perfect example of you get out what you put in.

Bob was one of the best professors I ever had. His lectures were engaging and he gives students all of the tools they need in order to succeed in his class, so long as they access them first. It is also important to note that regular attendance at office hours greatly increases one's chances for success.

He is definitely the best teacher I've had so far in two years! I dreaded math but ended up actually understanding all the concepts. I was quite intimidated coming into class at first, but by the end of the semester I left feeling confident with calculus. He definitely prepares you well for further calculus courses. Do well on quizzes!
Awesome teacher overall. If you put in the time and effort, he'll definitely help you out at office hours. Great lectures and very easy to talk to, and his grading process is very lenient overall.

The best math teacher I have ever had. His explanations are very clear and he breaks down difficult concepts in ways that are  clear and understandable. However, he will make you work for your grade. I ended up with an A, but I had to put a lot of effort in. Definitely take Calc 1 with him if you truly want to understand the material.
The professor is a great person. He tries to make sure everyone who whats to succeed succeeds. But it is up to you on how much your willing to work. This class is a lot of work.
Great Lectures and Most of the tests weren't too bad at all just gotta do the work

He's the best math teacher I've ever had period. He is very clear and concise. One thing that I would advise is don't slack on quizzes. That probably killed my grade in the end. I got B's on the midterms with about 3 days of work but a D in my quiz section (which is worth 1 midterm altogether).

Easily the best math instructor I've had in my entire life. Explains things clearly and in a manner "a kindergartner could understand," which is how teaching should be done. Of course, have precalc taken care of before. Also, do the "optional" HW; without it, you will do poorly. Be prepped for time crunch quizzes and use the free math tutoring!
